rComments: There's a lot of reading to be done for this class (it is a literature class) but she is a very intentional caring prof. I had her as a TA in 1100 and a prof in 1120 and she is incredibly dedicated to her students. And the content of the course is relevant, we explored works from not just white authors. Also ask for extensions! She gives them!

Had her in first year, and she was a TA, but she led the DGD on her own. Such a kind, kind person, and really funny after everyone got comfortable. She will really do so much more than she needs to and it's really appreciated. Love her. So happy she is a prof on her own now.
I still don't understand how the assignments were graded, the prof was extra tough for no apparent reason, and the content was boring.. It just all got repetitive after a while.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: She is very kind and understands what everyone is going through. She's pretty lenient with due dates, so if you've got some issues with deadlines, it doesn't hurt to ask. There's a few short stories and a 200-page novel that I had to read for all the assignments and final, but the class was overall light
